<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The door opened to reveal a hunched figure, covered in a long flowing dark robe. The hood was so deep, that not even the figures facial features could be seen. The robe was glistening with moisture, the rain having fully soaked the material. The figure floated in through the doorway with barely a ripple of movement showing. The patrons near the door felt an un-natural wave of cold wash over them as the figure passed. A scullery maid looked to the floor with a frown expecting to see a trail of water from the soaking robes, but instead saw only worms and insects scurrying on the floor behind the figure. Reaching the far wall where public notices were pinned over one another in organized confusion, the figure raised a skeletal hand, and placed a piece of parchament upon the board. It read..</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Creatures of Norrath,<br>
<br>
We of the Eurydice, seek any and all of the surname Vex. This family name is thought to be of Ak'Anon. Great reward will be unto those who provide information regarding those who bear this name.<br>
<br>
Plague Seeker of Eurydice</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>As the dark figure lowered its hand, the robe simply fell to the floor. Within seconds the robe too was gone, leaving only a mound of maggots, insects and worms, which quickly found their way into the nooks and crannies of the floor boards. <br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Kerridwynn strolled through the bar, stopping to grab a bottle of wine from the barkeep. This was her first visit to this place, and she was curious as to the goings-on. She paused at the far wall to read the notices.<br>
<br>
As she read, her eyebrows shot up, and a look of recognition crossed her face. Turning, she tossed a couple of plat at the barkeep and took off out the door, for Harvester Hall. <br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
A pair of pale grey eyes hover outside the walls of the Harvesters of Darkness. For days, the commings and goings have been closely watched, unknown to those inside. There is no movement or emotion in the eyes for what seems like an eternity. Then, on the fifth day, the eyes whirl and narrow, to see a gnome approaching the Harvesters hall. Spectral eyelids close, and when they open the twin orbs are behind the gnome, studying him intently, seeing through him, commiting every detail to memory. The small bonedancer reaches the doors to the hall and enters, seemingly oblivious to the presence. For the second time the eyelids close, and the presence is gone from the world<br>
<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;Mistress Escron, it is true. The blood line lives.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell me everything.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>She said<br>
<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;The son of Binuven hid the flesh in Ak'Anon as we suspected, but it appears to have matured much sooner than anticipated. It resides now among the Teir' Dal, and follows our Lord. Perhaps we underestimated...?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>A wave of agony that only those of the planes could see, washed over the incorpreal body of Avhi Escron's servant.<br>
<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;Bring the flesh here&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>She hissed</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;And the companions of the flesh?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;If they knew, they would have destroyed it by now. Leave them be.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;As you command&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The spectral eyes closed, and were gone, back to Neriak.<br>
<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Kerridwynn strides into Harvester Hall, walking purposefully towards the small closet the gnome bonedancer has claimed as his own. She pauses briefly, knocking on the door. As soon as she hears the sleepy gnome answer her knock, she pulls open the door.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Flacon, I've recently come from the Hero Heart Tavern, a place I've never been, but that's beside the point. I was most interested to see a notice upon their wall, asking for information on any bearing the name of Vex.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn studies the gnome, her eyes glowing in the semi-darkness.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Anything you wish the share with me?&quot; <br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The sickly gnome slumps his shoulders as he lets out a sigh.<br>
<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;Forgive me M'lady. I have never discussed my past for two reasons. First, I don't really know that much myself, and secondly, nobody ever asked. All I can say is this...<br>
<br>
The only record of my past is a torn piece of parchment written in the hand of someone named Llaorn Vex. It is nearly destroyed with time, but some remains. I believe this person to be my birth father, but as I never knew my parents I cannot be sure. Most of what I know comes from my companions in the Dark Reflection, where I was raised, and from my own research. I will gladly fetch the charge and my notes for you if you wish.&quot;<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn nods.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;I think you'd better bring everything you have to my office. Someone is very interested in you, and perhaps we need to figure out why, eh?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn turns towards the stairs, stopping a servant.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Bring some bottles and glasses up to my chambers, you know what I prefer to drink, and I'm sure you know Master Flacon's preferences as well. I want to see it all in my office before he reaches my threshold, understood?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The servant bows slightly and rushes off. Kerridwynn turns back to Flacon.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Please, meet with me in my office shortly. I would take a look at this information of yours. Something stalks Harvester Hall, I can feel it. We need to be prepared.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn nods to Flacon, and disappears up the stairs to her office. <br>
<br>
