<br>
For what seemed like an enternity, Flacon floated in an ocean of black blood. There was no sound or sight, just the numbness and fatigue of his ordeal. It was bliss. There was no more pain, just.. floating.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
The sickly gnome was floating. Floating in an endless black. It suddenly occured to the Necromancer that his lungs were not drawing breath. He had no idea how long he had gone without air. Seconds perhaps? minutes? Eons? He had no idea, but knew at the most basic levels of consciousness that he had to breath, so he drew a breath. Instantly the warm ocean of black was gone, replaced by the searing hot light of pain. His eyelids, fluttered open ever so slowly revealing the whites of his eyes. Slowly, the pupils sank down and he became more and more aware of his surroundings. He was lying on his back, strapped to a large block of wood. The block itself was a red stain of dried blood, rust colored seepage all along the sides from centuries of exposure to blood from all the races. Even the heart of the block, some eighteen inches deep, was moist with blood.<br>
<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;Do you know why you have been sick your whole life bonedancer?&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Avhi chided<br>
<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;You have within your blood my greatest gift to the world. Your blood is tainted with the most potent of my dark plagues. The Darkness that I gave to the world, the darkness that brought me here to our Lord Bertoxxulous' realm, you have in your flesh....<br>
<br>
And I want it back.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Avhi, dressed in what appeared to be a gown of bleeding human flesh, walked over to Flacon. The sickly gnome watched, helpless, and she raised her hand over his chest, palm down. Slowly, her bony fingers curled, as if gripping an orange. Pale yellow light began to colligate between her fingers as the words of the ancients sprang from her lips. Tendrils of what looked like yellowish green smoke were drawn from the gnome's flesh, drawn into the growing ball of sickly yellow light. Flacon's back arched so quickly and so violetly that both his lungs collapsed. He tried to scream, but with no breath all that came out was a sickening gurgle of black blood. Avhi's hand, now fully encompassed in the essence she took from flacon, trembled with the power and energy that it contained. Avhi's eyes gleamed with resolute satisfaction as she moved her hand towards her stomach. Without hesitaion or reaction, she plunged the hand into her flesh, moaning softly as her skin took on a sickly hue. <br>
<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;Your destiny is now one step closer to being complete bonedancer. Your grandfather will take you back.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I do not believe he survived&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>said Binuven, as he looked to the lifeless body on the wood block.<br>
<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;My Lord is not finished with this one yet, even if I am. The Teir' Dal female has the ability to revive him. Dispose of it. There is much to do, now that I am complete once more.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Avhi turned and was gone, leaving the spectral eyes and the now lifeless Flacon alone.<br>
<br>
